wikipedia_page.main: Ann Walker (20 May 1803 – 25 February 1854) was an Englishwoman, notionally married in Britain’s first known lesbian wedding, to diarist and fellow Yorkshire landowner Anne Lister at Holy Trinity Church, Goodramgate, York, which bears a commemorative plaque. She was the owner of Crow Nest, in Calderdale, close to Lister’s estate Shibden Hall. The two of them were travelling abroad when Lister died.
